# CODEOWNERS — auto-assign reviewers to PRs touching specific paths.
#
# GitHub looks at the *last matching pattern* per file, so order
# from most general to most specific. Lines starting with `#` are
# comments; blank lines are ignored.
#
# Locale review routing
# ---------------------
# Translation PRs need at least one native-speaker review before
# merging. Each locale routes to a small reviewer team named
# `@zyra-project/terraviz-i18n-<locale>`. Add yourself by opening
# a PR against this file with the team you want to join (or start);
# without a review team, locales stay in `experimental` status —
# reachable via `?locale=<code>` query flag for testing but hidden
# from the public Tools → Language picker.
#
# See CONTRIBUTING-TRANSLATIONS.md for the full reviewer workflow.

# Spanish — L1 seed locale.
